channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Lyndon B Johnson’s presidency began when JFK was assassinated in 1963
item.description: Lyndon B. Johnson became the 36th President of the United States after the assassination of John F. Kennedy in 1963; Johnson ran in his own right in 1964, winning in a landslide.

item.title: RFK Jr. asked to join Trump's transition team
item.description: The former Democrat told Tucker Carlson that he wants the job and will "work to get Trump elected."

item.title: Trump Is Likely Right about Illegal Immigrants Accounting for Job Growth
item.description: Large-scale immigration allows us to ignore the deterioration in labor-force participation.

item.title: Tim Walz’s Malignant Lies Disqualify Him From Being Anywhere Near Power
item.description: For the Minnesota governor and far-left vice presidential candidate, the truth is fluid in the laboratory of manufactured facts.

item.title: 2024 Countdown: Harris has post-DNC momentum but Trump is burning up campaign trail with 10 weeks left
item.description: Former President Trump and Vice President Harris entering the final sprint in their 2024 White House showdown as Tuesday marks 10 weeks until Election Day on Nov. 5.

item.title: Judge accepts insanity plea from man who attacked Virginia congressman's office with bat
item.description: A northern Virginia man who attacked staffers in the district office of U.S. Rep. Gerry Connolly with a baseball bat was found not guilty by reason of insanity Monday.

item.title: Republicans Need to Take a Stand on Abortion
item.description: At a minimum, Donald Trump should commit to vetoing any federal legislation to enact a national right to abortion or to expand taxpayer funding.

item.title: High School To Expel Tennis Star For Reporting Desk Graffiti In Junior High
item.description: Politics or punishment? As her Moms for Liberty mother makes waves on school board

item.title: Police vote key to election as cops weigh 'lawlessness vs law and order' on ballot: retired chief
item.description: Retired Illinois Police Chief Tom Weitzel spoke to Fox News Digital about the police vote for the 2024 election and how law enforcement votes could sway the election.

item.title: Democrats sue to block Georgia election rules that they warn will block finalization of results
item.description: Georgia's Democratic Party sued Monday to block two recent rules adopted by the State Election Board that could be used by county officials who want to refuse to certify an election, potentially causing delays in finalizing the state's results.

item.title: The Great Price-Gouging Walk-Back
item.description: Don’t mind her, she’s just trying to say things that sound good.

item.title: Democrats Lose Ploy To Remove Green Party Ticket From Wisconsin Ballot
item.description: 'Big win against the anti-Democratic Party’s war on democracy and voter choice!' Green Party presidential candidate Jill Stein wrote on X.

item.title: GOP governor rips Harris after analysis reveals eye-popping cost of illegal immigration in state: 'Disaster'
item.description: One state in the United States is spending more than $100 million a year on the illegal immigrants that have entered its borders, according to a new report.

item.title: Colorado GOP chairman ousted in a contentious vote that he dismisses as a 'sham'
item.description: Colorado GOP Chairman Dave Williams, who has tried to push the state party to extremes, was ousted over the weekend in a vote that he called illegitimate, precipitating a leadership standoff as the November election looms.

item.title: How Radical Will Kamala Harris’s Tax Policy Be? Look to Her Past
item.description: The Democratic presidential nominee has only begun to outline her 2024 tax proposals. But her far-left 2020 agenda could provide some hints.

item.title: Under Tim Walz, Minnesota Banned Christians From Teaching In Public Schools
item.description: Walz is poised to make similar bigoted, totalitarian, and unconstitutional policies across the United States should he be elected vice president.

item.title: Vermont GOP sees ‘record’ ballot boost as blue-state citizens ‘see the need for change’
item.description: Republicans in Vermont expressed optimism after dozens of residents met the write-in threshold to make the November general election ballot following the primary.

item.title: Judge puts Biden's illegal immigrant spouse 'parole' program on hold
item.description: A federal judge issued an order Monday halting President Biden's new deportation amnesty for illegal-immigrant spouses of U.S. citizens, saying it makes sense to keep the program on ice until courts can decide whether it is legal.

item.title: Florida’s Flawed Beef with Cultivated Meat
item.description: The kind of meat that Florida has banned may or may not catch on. But consumers, not lobbyists, should determine whether it does.

item.title: In Yet Another Middle Finger To Taxpayers, McConnell Nets Kentucky $500 Million In Earmarks
item.description: Only someone like McConnell could use his impending departure from the leadership ranks to act even more swampy.
